# Data Directory Rules

## Data Organization
- Use clear, descriptive file names
- Organize data by type, source, or date
- Maintain consistent naming conventions
- Use appropriate file formats for different data types

## Data Quality
- Validate data before processing
- Document data sources and lineage
- Maintain data integrity and consistency
- Handle missing or corrupted data appropriately
- Version control data schemas and transformations

## Data Security
- Never store sensitive data in plain text
- Use appropriate access controls
- Encrypt data at rest when necessary
- Follow data privacy regulations (GDPR, CCPA, etc.)
- Implement proper data retention policies

## Data Processing
- Document all data transformations
- Use reproducible data processing pipelines
- Maintain audit trails for data changes
- Test data processing scripts thoroughly
- Handle large datasets efficiently

## File Management
- Use appropriate file formats (CSV, JSON, Parquet, etc.)
- Compress large files when appropriate
- Maintain backup copies of important data
- Clean up temporary files regularly
- Document file dependencies and relationships

## Data Documentation
- Include README files for datasets
- Document data schemas and field definitions
- Maintain data dictionaries
- Record data quality metrics
- Document any data cleaning or preprocessing steps 